@{
    ViewData["Title"] = "Privacy Policy";
}

<div class="container mt-5">
    <div class="privacy-policy-card shadow-lg p-5 rounded">
        <h1 class="text-center mb-4 text-primary">Privacy Policy</h1>

        <p class="lead text-center">
            Welcome to AnyoneForTennis! We’re here to "serve" you the best experience while keeping your personal data protected. We take privacy as seriously as a match point, and we promise not to "drop the ball" when it comes to your information.
        </p>

        <h3 class="text-success mt-5">1. Information We Collect</h3>
        <p>
            When you "lob" your details our way, we gather various types of data to ensure our services are always in "top spin" condition. Here’s the "racket" of what we collect:
        </p>
        <ul>
            <li><strong>Personal Identification Data:</strong> Your name, email address, and other contact details – because even off the court, we like to stay in touch.</li>
            <li><strong>Technical Data:</strong> Like your IP address, browser type, and device info – helping us keep our website "ace" and your experience smooth.</li>
            <li><strong>Usage Data:</strong> How you navigate the site – or should we say, how you "rally" around our pages.</li>
        </ul>

        <h3 class="text-success mt-5">2. How We Use Your Information</h3>
        <p>
            We’re not here to "string" you along. We use your information to keep our services in "court-ready" shape:
        </p>
        <ul>
            <li>Provide, maintain, and enhance our services – so you never "miss a shot."</li>
            <li>Respond to inquiries and support requests – because we’re always "at your service."</li>
            <li>Keep you updated about changes – no surprises here, just "net" gains.</li>
            <li>Analyze usage patterns – to ensure our site stays in "match-winning" form.</li>
        </ul>

        <h3 class="text-success mt-5">3. Sharing Your Information</h3>
        <p>
            We keep your data in the "sweet spot" and won’t share it unless we’re required by law or you give us the "go-ahead." Our service providers are bound to "play by the rules" and protect your data just like we do.
        </p>

        <h3 class="text-success mt-5">4. Data Security</h3>
        <p>
            We’ve got "love" for data security. We implement safeguards to ensure your information is "smash-proof." While no system is completely "faultless," we’re committed to staying ahead of the "baseline" to protect your privacy.
        </p>

        <h3 class="text-success mt-5">5. Your Rights</h3>
        <p>
            You’ve got the "right to volley" any questions our way about how your data is handled. Want to access, correct, or delete your info? Just give us a "serve" at our contact email.
        </p>

        <h3 class="text-success mt-5">6. Changes to This Policy</h3>
        <p>
            If we make any "game-changing" updates to our privacy policy, we’ll let you know so you won’t be caught "off-court." Keep an eye out for notifications; we wouldn’t want you to "miss the ball."
        </p>

        <h3 class="text-success mt-5">7. Contact Us</h3>
        <p>
            Got questions? Want to chat about privacy? We’re "all ears" and ready to "racket" up some answers. Contact us anytime, and we’ll make sure to keep things in "play."
        </p>

        <footer class="text-center mt-5">
            <p class="text-muted">&copy; 2024 AnyoneForTennis. All rights reserved. Keep your data secure and your "love" for tennis alive. Remember, privacy is always "game, set, match" for us!</p>
        </footer>
    </div>
</div>

<!-- Custom Styles for the Privacy Policy Page -->
<style>
    .container {
        max-width: 900px;
    }

    .privacy-policy-card {
        background: linear-gradient(145deg, #f0fff0, #d8ffd8);
        border-radius: 20px;
        border: 2px solid #28a745;
        padding: 40px;
        box-shadow: 0px 4px 15px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.2);
        position: relative;
        overflow: hidden;
    }

    h1 {
        font-size: 2.8rem;
        color: #007bff;
        font-weight: bold;
    }

    h3 {
        font-size: 1.8rem;
        color: #28a745;
        margin-top: 30px;
        text-decoration: underline;
    }

    p, ul {
        font-size: 1.2rem;
        color: #444;
        line-height: 1.6;
    }

    ul {
        margin-top: 15px;
        padding-left: 20px;
    }

        ul li {
            margin-bottom: 10px;
        }

    .lead {
        font-size: 1.4rem;
        font-weight: 300;
    }

    footer {
        margin-top: 50px;
        border-top: 2px solid #ddd;
        padding-top: 20px;
        color: #555;
    }

    .text-primary {
        color: #007bff !important;
    }

    .text-success {
        color: #28a745 !important;
    }

    .privacy-policy-card h3:before {
        content: "🎾 ";
        font-size: 1.2em;
        color: #28a745;
    }

    .privacy-policy-card h1:before {
        content: "🏆 ";
        font-size: 1.5em;
        color: #007bff;
    }

    .privacy-policy-card h1:after {
        content: " 🏆";
        font-size: 1.5em;
        color: #007bff;
    }

    /* Bouncing Tennis Ball Animation */
    .tennis-ball {
        position: absolute;
        width: 50px;
        height: 50px;
        background: url('/img/ball.png') no-repeat center center / cover;
        border-radius: 50%;
        animation: bounce 4s infinite cubic-bezier(0.5, 0.05, 1, 0.5);
        opacity: 0.8;
    }

    @@keyframes bounce {
        0%, 100% {
            top: 0;
            left: 0;
            transform: translateY(0);
        }
        50% {
            top: 70%;
            left: 90%;
            transform: translateY(-20px);
        }
    }
</style>

<!-- Tennis Ball Element -->
<div class="tennis-ball"></div>
